RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEL MOON was prominent into the first turn, ceded the lead content to press from inside, lost ground into the far turn, asked midway on that bend, regained nearly even terms inside the leader in upper stretch, dueled in close quarters while possibly brushing with that one, inched past late. PARABELLUM set the pace off the rail, went in the two to three path, dueled through the lane, was outfinished. MAJOR GRIFFIN settled outside to stalk, raced four to five wide throughout, gained slowly but steadily in the stretch however needed more. GREAT REALIZATION switched out leaving the first turn to stalk from outside three wide, took closer order to reach striking distance coming to the quarter pole three deep but could not sustain the effort in the stretch. BILLHILL was taken back and shifted in entering the first turn, raced at the rear in the two to three path on both bends, failed to rally. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.NAME: Great Realization
ENTRY.COMMENT: switched out 1st turn, 3wide bid, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Del Moon
ENTRY.COMMENT: ceded lead, tracked insd-2p, ask 5/16, duel str, inched past

ENTRY.NAME: Parabellum
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace off rail, 2-3path, duel, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Billhill
ENTRY.COMMENT: shifted in, 2-3path turns, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Major Griffin
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside, 4-5wide, slow gain, needed more

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25200. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUBY THE DESTROYER set the pace racing off the rail, was asked coming to the top of stretch and responded by drawing clear and widening through upper stretch, was kept to the task and held safe. GOSPEL FABULOUS broke outwardly bothering a rival and was steadied at the start, shifted in reserved at the rear racing in the three to four path early, angled five wide coming to the quarter pole, could not gain on the winner but was clearly second best. MISS LONG LEGS stalked three wide just off the eventual winner, was asked for run inside a foe within striking distance coming to the five-sixteenths, failed to rally but was best of the rest. CREES VALENTYME stalked from outside four wide, steadily weakened in the stretch. SKY ECHO tracked just off the leaders inside, came out a bit for the drive, failed to rally. ALTERNATE ABBY got away slowly and was bothered at the start, moved forward outside rivals five through the first turn and early up the backstretch to reach the flank of the leader, began to drop back outside foes on the far turn, faltered and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Sky Echo
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Ruby the Destroyer
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace off rail, drew off when asked, kept task

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Long Legs
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3wide, ask 5/16, no rally, best of rest

ENTRY.NAME: Gospel Fabulous
ENTRY.COMMENT: bump foe, stdy'd brk, 3-4path early, angled 5w 1/4, second best

ENTRY.NAME: Alternate Abby
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slowly & bothered brk, forward outside 5wide, faltered

ENTRY.NAME: Crees Valentyme
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 4wide, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 84. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022-2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $7,500. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 27 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Pr ice $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNITED PATRIOT set the pace racing off the rail with moderate outside pressure early, edged clear about the nine-sixteenths, faced a challenger and was asked for more past the quarter pole, headed by that one at the top of the stretch and put to stronger urging, came back inside the sixteenth to nab the win. CANEY'S GHOST settled just off the leading pack tracking from inside, edged nearer and moved out three wide past the quarter pole, struck the lead at the top of the stretch, dueled from outside still with a head in front but was outfinished. GOT MOJO exchanged a very light brush at the start, raced off the pace in the three to four path, was asked for more past the three-eighths, ran on but was no threat to the top two. REACH THE CIRCLE brushed lightly at the start, pressed the winner from outside three wide, began to drop back leaving the backstretch, steadily weakened. WAVERUNNER brushed very lightly after the start, angled in and was reserved in the two path, failed to rally. BAOZUN exchanged a very light brush after the start, pursued from outside five wide, steadily dropped back, was pulled up in upper- to mid-stretch and vanned off. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.NAME: Caney's Ghost
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, tracked inside, came out 3w, led 3/16-1/16, outfinished

ENTRY.COMMENT: pace off rail, pressured, clear 9/16, ask 1/4, headed, resurgent

ENTRY.NAME: Reach the Circle
ENTRY.COMMENT: light brush brk, pressed winner 3w, weakened

ENTRY.COMMENT: light brush brk, 3-4path, ask past 3/8, no match top pair

ENTRY.NAME: Waverunner
ENTRY.COMMENT: light brush after brk, reserved in 2path, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Baozun
ENTRY.COMMENT: light brush after brk, outside 5w, pulled up, vanned off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Purse 25000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR OKLAHOMA STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADRIA was quick to the fore to take command and dictate terms in the clear racing just off the rail, turned back a challenger late on the turn, was clear into upper stretch and asked for more, kept to the task and held sway. LINGERING PROMISE got away alertly then allowed a rival to go forward content to stalk that one, took closer order on the turn drawing alongside the flank of the eventual winner racing three wide, proved no match for that one but second best. LACEY BOSS tracked from inside on or just off the rail, came out about four wide turning for home and put to urging, ran on for show honors three to four wide in the stretch but unable to threaten the top ones. OKIE FRONT settled racing off the pace between runners in the second flight into the turn, moved out five wide turning for home, ran on evenly. ROZEY CHEEKS trailed racing off the inside, went in the five path through the turn, angled in once in upper stretch and failed to menace. MARIA ELENA Y. G was ridden along outside runners four wide on the turn, weakened and came up empty. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION FINAL TIME WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.COMMENT: ridden along 4w turn, weakened, empty

ENTRY.COMMENT: away alertly, stalked, mild bid 3w 5/16, no match, 2nd best

ENTRY.COMMENT: off inside, 5path turn, angled in upper, no menace

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since December 27 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE'S FIRE AND ICE pressed the pace then applied more pressure three wide up the backstretch, dueled outside three then two wide on the far turn taking command by the three-sixteenths, forged clear under urging. BID FOR POWER was bumped lightly at the break but moved forward to set the pace racing a path removed from the rail, faced pressure up the backstretch, moved nearer the rail late on the far turn, was no match for the winner but second best. DIXIELAND CANDY settled three to four wide off the early pace, advanced between runners two wide on the far turn, came out four wide for the stretch drive and ran on. SATURDAY SERVICE bumped a rival at the start, tracked from inside, saved ground on both turns, came out a bit for the stretch run and failed to rally. MUSICAL MILLIE raced outside off the pace four to five wide throughout and failed to menace. CAMCORDIA shifted in two to three wide early and advanced forward between rivals up the backstretch, asked by the quarter pole racing three deep through the far turn and came up empty. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION FINAL TIME WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.COMMENT: bump foe brk, inside, came out str, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Bid for Power
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped brk, pace off rail, no match, 2nd best

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed, prompted, 2-3w command 3/16, forged clear

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled 3-4w early, advanced btw 2nd turn, 4w str, ran on

Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Multiple Winners Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIGHTINGTEMPTATION prompted the pace from outside then from between runners up the backstretch, raced two to three wide contending to the top of the stretch, was headed in mid-stretch while drifting out a bit, dug in and surged late to prevail inside over KACHINA, who moved forward three to four wide early, prompted the pace from outside up the backstretch, continued to contend through the far turn, took command nearing the eighth pole, drifted out a bit in upper- to mid-stretch, was outfinished. OH NIKI vied inside on or just off the rail, was no match for the top pair. BILLIE G tracked off the leaders near inside, ran evenly and made no bid. LENA'S SHADOW rated between rivals in the second flight up the backstretch having travelled two to four wide to that juncture, continued between foes on the far turn and put to some urging, angled five wide into the stretch, failed to rally. RIVER LIBERTY raced outside four to six wide throughout, moved up closer to the leaders early up the backstretch, soon dropped back to race outside the second group and had no rally.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rated btw, 2-4w, angled 5w into str, no rally

ENTRY.COMMENT: outside, 4-6w throughout, early advance, dropped back, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 21000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGNET AND STEEL was coaxed to more forward position at the start then settled in to track from inside, found room cutting the corner to bid inside turning for home, took command by the three-sixteenths, was soon challenged by outside rivals and put to stronger urging, was stoutly challenged past the sixteenth pole but dug in to hold those rivals at bay. BOLD COURAGE stalked from outside going four wide on the turn, bid about the sixteenth pole but was outfinished. MANDOLIN WIND broke a step slowly, advanced into the turn racing about three to four deep, went four to five wide on the turn still gaining, drifted in through the stretch, made a mild bid about a sixteenth out but appeared to hang while clearly best of the rest. SAZON was forwardly-positioned pressing three wide, went between rivals and asked to keep up three furlongs from home, steadily weakened. LITTLE SOLDIER BOY chased from outside, asked for more midway on the turn moving out from five to six wide late on that bend, came into upper stretch seven deep and was never near enough to threaten. RAINBOW CREST had the early lead setting the pace in the two path, was pressured thoroughly into the turn, wilted in upper stretch. SCRIMSHIRE got away a step slowly, moved out off the inside into the turn while moving forward on the leaders, swung six wide into upper stretch and failed to menace.

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, rail bid, led by 3/16, dug in, held foes

CAT TALE SKY raced at the back near the inside, came two to three wide in upper stretch and put to urging, got up for second over CAT TALE BREEZE, who set a pressured pace inside on or just off the rail, could not kick on with the winner and lost place late. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Miranda Diane S. WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 87. Stakes Purse 55000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Nominations close Thursday, March 16, 2023. No nomination fee. $500 to pass the entry box. Starters to pay additional $250 with $55,000 guaranteed - $20,000 from WRD purse account , $25,000 from TRAO, $5,000 from the Oklahoma-Bred Program and $5,000 from OBF Breeders Awards. $50,000 of the $55,000 guaranteed money will be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Oklahoma-Bred money to b e divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weights: Three-Year-Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of $30,000 twice in 2022-23 allowed 3 lbs.; of $30,000 once in 2022-23, 6 lbs. Starters to be named th rough the entry box by usual time of entry. This race will be limited to 12 starters. In the event the race overfills, highest earnings in 2022-23 shall be preferred. There will be no also-eligibles. A suitable award will be presented to the winning owne
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAGAN'S JET moved clear soon after the break to dictate terms, was put to urging in the stretch and kept to task late to hold. SINNIN N GRINNIN pursued two to three wide through the turn, was put to strong urging in upper stretch, drifted out a bit in mid-stretch, gained steadily but too little too late. DICEY settled toward the back, advanced on the turn inside rivals but off the fence, moved out three wide by the quarter pole, was carried out a bit near the furlong grounds, finished up willingly but needed more. GOTTA SEE RED chased from outside, failed to rally. PLENTY OF VISION got away several lengths slowly, raced inside and was not a factor.

TERAWATT got away well, was prominent early but steadily eased back off the leaders racing off the inside about three deep into the turn, finished willingly but was second best. FIRE EXTINGUISHER was off the pace and forced four to five wide on the turn, angled in to the two path in upper stretch and kicked on willingly to be gaining but too late. ROMANCER was caught six to seven wide on the turn and improved position. ROBERT WHO got away well, moved to the fore soon after the start, set the pace facing pressure while racing just off the rail, weakened. MUCHO BLING had brief early speed among the early leaders two wide, dropped back into the turn, had no late kick but ran on evenly. G'S STORM broke a bit awkwardly and was ridden along but lacking speed, went five to six wide on the turn, passed tired foes. TRADE DEADLINE raced evenly while off the inside part of the course and made no bid. ORNERY AS HELL chased from outside just off the leaders going four to five wide on the turn and came up empty. TWILITE LIASON chased mid-pack, faded.
